AYN Odin 2 Qualcomm Sensor Core data

The regular Odin 2 uses an ST LSM6DSV IMU owned by Qualcomm's ADSP Sensor
Core. Batocera starts the stock SensorsPD and RootPD FastRPC listeners, then
publishes accelerometer and gyroscope samples through the shared DSU bridge.

Unlike Thor's SH5001 profile, the selected Odin 2 registry already exists in
the unit's Android persist partition. On the first Batocera sensor startup,
S28qcom-sensors mounts that partition read-only with journal replay disabled,
validates the LSM6DSV selection, and copies the registry to
/userdata/system/qcom-sensors/odin2. Android persist is never modified and the
Batocera copy is never replaced automatically, preserving learned per-unit
calibration. Subsequent boots do not need to mount Android persist.

The generic Kailua sensor configuration and sns_tppe.so helper are shared with
Thor. Odin 2 retains its own version-1 sns_reg.conf and its own ADSP firmware
under /lib/firmware/qcom/sm8550/ayn/odin2.

Motion bridge
-------------

The Odin 2 profile maps its unrotated LSM6DSV stream into the shared console
DSU frame. With controls facing up, raw gravity appears on -Z; the left and top
edges appear on +X and +Y. The validated DSU accelerometer mapping is therefore
(X, Z, Y), with the corresponding axial-vector gyroscope mapping
(-X, Z, Y). S29qcom-motion selects this profile automatically from
"ayn,odin2" and exposes slot 0 on 127.0.0.1:26760.

Calibration is stored in
/userdata/system/qcom-sensors/odin2/motion-calibration.ini using frame
"odin2-dsu-v2". The shared "Odin 2 / Thor Sensor Calibration" entry in Tools
collects a stationary gyro zero and five safe accelerometer poses without a
face-down step.

Cold-boot validation on a regular AYN Odin 2 confirmed concurrent AYN-Odin2
audio, supervised SensorsPD and RootPD listeners, raw LSM6DSV streams, DSU
delivery, pose calibration, and calibration reload after reboot. Run
`batocera-qcom-sensors-test 5` for a complete smoke test.
